<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,871,1293]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
DISTRIBUTION. Mediterranean coast of N Africa from 
<collectingCountry box="[753,837,980,1005]" name="Algeria" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Algeria</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[872,942,980,1004]" name="Egypt" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Egypt</collectingCountry>
, through the Levant and 
<collectingCountry box="[1218,1314,980,1005]" name="Turkey" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
to western 
<collectingCountry box="[151,200,1016,1039]" name="Iran" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,871,1293]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3342274509" country="Iran" location="Mt. Damavand" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Kermanshah">
DISTRIBUTION IN 
<collectingCountry box="[355,411,1052,1075]" name="Iran" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">IRAN</collectingCountry>
. 
<figureCitation box="[429,528,1052,1077]" captionStart="FIGURES 140–145. 140" captionStartId="95.[151,264,1557,1580]" captionTargetBox="[171,1416,213,1516]" captionTargetId="figure-54@95.[151,1436,193,1536]" captionTargetPageId="95" captionText="FIGURES 140–145. 140. Trachylepis septemtaeniata. 141. Trachylepis vittata. 142. Pristurus rupestris. Blue square denotes the type locality for P. r. iranicus. 143. Teratoscincus bedriagai. 144. Teratoscincus keyserlingii. 145. Teratoscincus microlepis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4929781" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4929781/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fig. 141</figureCitation>
. Scattered records from 
<collectingRegion box="[813,954,1052,1077]" country="Iran" name="Kermanshah" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Kermanshah</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1016,1140,1052,1077]" country="Iran" name="Ilam" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Ilam Prov.</collectingRegion>
, an isolated single record from 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C387F2FFA3FF96FF5B4C4553E4FAA1:8EB5603FFFA3FF96FF184B625707FBF4" box="[212,383,1087,1112]" country="Iran" name="Mt. Damavand" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" stateProvince="Kermanshah">Mt. Damavand</location>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[394,600,1087,1112]" country="Iran" name="Mazandaran" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Mazandaran Prov.</collectingRegion>
Iran represents the eastern margin of the species distribution
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,871,1293]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
HABITAT. Dry stony slopes with annual grassy vegetation (
<bibRefCitation author="Fathinia, B. &amp; Rastegar-Pouyani, N. &amp; Sampour, M. &amp; Bahrami, A. M. &amp; Jaafari, G." box="[811,1035,1124,1149]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="65 - 79" refId="ref50340" refString="Fathinia, B., Rastegar-Pouyani, N., Sampour, M., Bahrami, A. M. &amp; Jaafari, G. (2009) The lizard fauna of the Ilam province, southwestern Iran. Iranian Journal of Animal Biosystematics, 5, 65 - 79." type="journal article" year="2009">
Fathinia 
<emphasis box="[911,961,1124,1149]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">et al</emphasis>
. 2009
</bibRefCitation>
). Outside 
<collectingCountry box="[1148,1193,1124,1147]" name="Iran" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Iran</collectingCountry>
reported from a wide variety of biotopes on stony or sandy soil from palm oases, field and road margins, or vegetated rocky slopes to places nearly devoid of any vegetation (
<bibRefCitation author="Schleich, H. H. &amp; Kastle, W. &amp; Kabisch, K." box="[597,825,1196,1221]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" refId="ref64677" refString="Schleich, H. H., Kastle, W. &amp; Kabisch, K. (1996) Amphibians and Reptiles of North Africa. Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein, 630 pp." type="book" year="1996">
Schleich 
<emphasis box="[702,758,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
1996
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[151,1397,1231,1256]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="discussion">
